<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Compound_interest&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://laws.justice.gc.ca/en/showdoc/cs/I-15/bo-ga:s_6//en#anchorbo-ga:s_6" class="external free" title="http://laws.justice.gc.ca/en/showdoc/cs/I-15/bo-ga:s_6//en#anchorbo-ga:s_6" rel="nofollow">http://laws.justice.gc.ca/en/showdoc/cs/I-15/bo-ga:s_6//en#anchorbo-ga:s_6</a> Interest Act (Canada), <i>Department of Justice</i>. The Interest Act specifies that interest is not recoverable unless the mortgage loan contains a statement showing the rate of interest chargeable, "calculated yearly or half-yearly, not in advance." In practice, banks use the half-yearly rate.</li>
<li id="cite_note-r1728-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-r1728_1-0" title="">^</a></b> <i>This article incorporates content from the 1728</i> <a href="/wiki/Cyclopaedia,_or_Universal_Dictionary_of_Arts_and_Sciences" title="Cyclopaedia, or Universal Dictionary of Arts and Sciences">Cyclopaedia</a><i>, a publication in the <a href="/wiki/Public_domain" title="Public domain">public domain</a>.</i></li>
